footerLinks.title: 529 Tax Information
footerLinks.content: Most U.S. states offer full or partial income tax deductions or credits for contributions to a 529 plan. As of 2026, Georgia taxpayers can receive an state income tax deduction for contributions to a Path2College 529 Plan account up to $4,000 per year. Taxpayers in AZ, AR, KS, ME, MN, MO, MT, OH, PA can also receive a state income tax deduction.
